  "advising_notes": [
    "Honors & Honors Program: A student becomes eligible for graduation with honors by meeting the minimum GPA (usually 3.500) and course requirements established by the College of Letters and Science. To qualify for high or highest honors, students must also complete the History Department honors program with a GPA of 3.500 or above and write a thesis that meets the criteria for high honors or highest honors. Students apply to participate in the department honors program during the latter part of their junior year. Admissio",
    "Study Abroad & the History Major: The department strongly encourages interested students to pursue their studies abroad. While there are no specific required courses or prerequisites, students are urged to take at least one history course that touches upon the geographic area where they plan to study abroad before departing. To receive a history degree from UC Davis, students must complete at least 18 upper division units in the history major at UC Davis (which can also include HIS 101, HIS 102 Discontinued, HIS 103). The remain",
    "American History & Institutions: This University requirement can be satisfied by passing any one of the following HIS courses: Course List Code Title Units HIS 017AHistory of the United States4 HIS 017BHistory of the United States4 HIS 072AWomen & Gender in America, to 18654 HIS 072BWomen & Gender in America, 1865-Present4 HIS 170AColonial America4 HIS 170BThe American Revolution4 HIS 170CThe Early National Period, 1789-18154 HIS 171ASlavery, Society & Expansion in the Early U.S.4 HIS 171BCivil War Era4 HIS 172American Environm"
  ],
  "total_units": "60"
